{"key":"processedPost-13042831","value":{"id":13042831,"first":13031079,"last":13071311,"when":1281657491,"utime":"08/13/10 02:58 AM","content":"<blockquote>Quote:<br /><b>angel418 said:</b><br />so i have been growing for about 4-5 months now and i keep getting more and more contams.&nbsp; my 1st batch was only 1, 2nd batch 3,&nbsp; and my last batch which was my 6th, i did 40 plastic jars, all but like 7 or 8 contamed!!!!<br /></blockquote><br /><br />This is the reason I get livid with anger when I hear noobs say not to worry if you get contamination, and don't toss out the cakes because contaminant spores are in the air anyway.&nbsp; They are, but not in the numbers indoors that they are when a spot of green mold is allowed to puke a few trillion spores into your growing room.&nbsp; They stick to the walls, the curtains, the floor, and you.&nbsp; All it takes is one or two contaminated projects left in a room and it becomes very difficult to grow there.<br /><br />You need to wash the walls, carpet, etc., with a bleach solution to nuke the spores.&nbsp; When doing inoculations, always use a still air box and wear surgical gloves that have been washed with alcohol.&nbsp; Use a surgical mask and hair net.&nbsp; In short, make sure none of those contaminants can get into your jars.<br /><br />A pressure cooker isn't necessary with the brf tek, and won't help.&nbsp; Your contaminants are getting in after sterilization, probably at inoculation.<br />RR","title":"Re: how to get rid off a growing contam problem??","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}